Activity 4: Essential Google Cloud Infrastructure: Core Services
Lab: Implementing Cloud SQL   
Here’s a clear, step-by-step guide to complete your
🧪 Lab 4: Implementing Cloud SQL (WordPress + Proxy + Private IP) 👇

🧪 PART 1: Create Cloud SQL (MySQL) Instance
✅ Step 1: Open Cloud SQL
Go to Google Cloud Console
Navigate → Cloud SQL
Click Create Instance
✅ Step 2: Choose Database
Select MySQL
Edition: Enterprise
Version: MySQL 8.0
✅ Step 3: Configure Instance
Instance ID: wordpress-db
Root Password: Passw0rd1! (or your own)
Region: same as lab
Zone: Single zone
✅ Step 4: Machine Configuration
Choose:
General Purpose
1 vCPU, 3.75 GB RAM
✅ Step 5: Storage
Type: SSD
Size: 10 GB
✅ Step 6: Enable Private IP
Go to Connections
Select:
✅ Private IP
Network: default
Click Confirm network setup
✅ Step 7: Security
Enable:
✅ Allow unencrypted connections
✅ Step 8: Create Instance
Click Create
⏳ Wait until green check appears
🧪 PART 2: Create Database inside SQL
✅ Step 9: Create Database
Open wordpress-db
Go to Databases
Click Create Database

Enter:

Name: wordpress

Click Create

🧪 PART 3: Configure Cloud SQL Proxy (External Connection)
✅ Step 10: Open VM
Go to Compute Engine → VM instances
Click SSH for:
👉 wordpress-proxy
✅ Step 11: Install Proxy
wget https://dl.google.com/cloudsql/cloud_sql_proxy.linux.amd64 -O cloud_sql_proxy
chmod +x cloud_sql_proxy
✅ Step 12: Get Connection Name
Go to Cloud SQL → wordpress-db
Copy Instance Connection Name
✅ Step 13: Set Variable
export SQL_CONNECTION=your-connection-name

Check:

echo $SQL_CONNECTION
✅ Step 14: Start Proxy
./cloud_sql_proxy -instances=$SQL_CONNECTION=tcp:3306 &

✔️ Output:

Listening on 127.0.0.1:3306
🧪 PART 4: Connect WordPress (Using Proxy)
✅ Step 15: Get External IP
curl -H "Metadata-Flavor: Google" \
http://169.254.169.254/computeMetadata/v1/instance/network-interfaces/0/access-configs/0/external-ip
✅ Step 16: Open Browser

👉 Go to:

http://<wordpress-proxy-EXTERNAL-IP>
✅ Step 17: Configure WordPress

Enter:

Field	Value
Database	wordpress
Username	root
Password	your root password
Host	127.0.0.1

Click:
➡️ Submit → Run Installation

✅ Step 18: Finish Setup
Enter any:
Site name
Username
Password

✔️ WordPress site created

🧪 PART 5: Connect via Private IP (More Secure)
✅ Step 19: Get Private IP
Go to Cloud SQL → wordpress-db
Copy Private IP
✅ Step 20: Open Second VM
Go to Compute Engine
Open:
👉 wordpress-private-ip
✅ Step 21: Open Website

👉 In browser:

http://<wordpress-private-ip-EXTERNAL-IP>
✅ Step 22: Configure WordPress (Private IP)

Enter:

Field	Value
Database	wordpress
Username	root
Password	same password
Host	<SQL_PRIVATE_IP>

Click:
➡️ Submit

✅ Step 23: Result

✔️ Shows:
👉 “Already Installed!”

✔️ Means:

Connected successfully via Private IP
🎯 FINAL OUTPUT

✔ Cloud SQL instance created
✔ Database configured
✔ WordPress connected via:

Proxy (External method)
Private IP (Internal secure method)
